                        <bindingDesc>
                          <binding contemporary="true" xml:id="binding">
                            <decoNote xml:id="b1">The book is sewn on four sewing stations (two pairs) linked to wooden boards with a leather half cover.</decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial"><material key="wood"/><material key="leather"/></decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Cover">
                              The book has half cover made of a brown-reddish leather decorated with blind tooled motifs. <term key="singleStraightLine">Single straight lines</term> divide the space in squares within they cross, forming a "X".
                              On the right board, a <term key="singleCircle">single circle</term> is placed at the intersections between the lines.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="Endbands" color="brown black">
                              The codex has <term key="slitBraid">slit-braid</term>endbands sewn to the textblock with a thread of animal origin.
                              Not every quire has tiedowns. The quires that don't have tiedowns, don't have additional holes even.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b7">
                              The sewing is a chain-stitch on four sewing stations (two pairs). The sewing pattern is a variation of the <term key="patternA3">pattern A3</term> by Bozzacchi.
                              Along the fold of the first quire, for each pair of sewing station there is one long stitch without knots. In the second quire there are two long stitches.
                              The thread used for the sewing is of <term key="animalThread">animal origin</term>.
                            </decoNote>
                            <decoNote xml:id="b10" type="Other">
                              Parchment <term key="guard">guards</term> are found in <locus target="#q1 #q2 #q23">quires: 1, 2 and 23</locus>.
                            </decoNote>
                          </binding>
